description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a technician to join the physiotherapy rehabilitation team based at Farnham Hospital. This team is committed to providing first rate patient care with a proactive MDT and supporting the members of the team to achieve this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are a physiotherapy assistant with hospital inpatient experience either on acute or rehabilitation wards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wish to work as part of the physiotherapy community hospital rehabilitation team based in Farnham Hospital&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are interested in assisting physiotherapists in the assessment and rehabilitation of patients with a variety of conditions from Falls and Frailty to Neurological conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wish to work closely with other members of a specialist MDT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A friendly and professional department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An in –house training programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Involvement in the staff appraisal scheme, audit and quality assurance programme.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameBethan SpickettJob titleBand 7 Occupational TherapistEmail addressbethan.spickett@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
